==Vietnamese==
===Etymology===
{{vi-etym-sino|清||hv=y|thanh}}.
Attested as a variant of {{m|vi|xênh}} (as in {{m|vi|xênh xang}}) in ''Đại Nam Quấc âm tự vị'' (1895). The earlier meaning appears to be along the line of "neat (of appearance), graceful (of manner)", as in the (now obsolete?) compound {{m|vi|xinh lịch}} (cf. {{vi-link|thanh lịch||清歷}}).
